  "texts": [
    "The neoclassical framework suggests that total factor productivity growth is driven by exogenously determined technological change and labor augmentation (Birks 1984; Edquist and Henrekson 2006; Goodridge et al. 2018; Pozdnyakova et al. 2019).",
    "In the context of the digital economy, the Internet of Things replaces traditional factors of production and offers innovative solutions for the agriculture industry (Pozdnyakova et al. 201; Farooq et al. 2020).",
    "Unlike the traditional economy, where factors like factories and machines play distinct roles, the digital economy sees a less differentiated role for these traditional production factors.",
    "The Internet of Things, being adaptable and efficient, emerges as a new and well-suited factor of production for the digital world (Pozdnyakova et al. 2019; Farooq et al., 2020).",
    "It is a promising technology that simplifies life, saves time, and reduces costs (Whitmore et al. 2015)."
  ],
